details.description: Our vision for Waterbean Coffee is to create an environment where we are more than just another coffee shop. We’d love for you to think of us as an extension of your home or business. Whether you are simply grabbing a fast cup of coffee to go, having a meeting in our shop, going over schoolwork, or just hanging out, we want to be that place where everyone feels welcome.

reviews_data.review_text:
I got an iced coffee with vanilla syrup and a white chocolate cold foam... Unfortunately this is the worst coffee drink that I have ever gotten. I drink coffee everyday from different places all over town. Also this is
by far the most I have ever paid for an iced coffee.Typical drinks like this cost no more than $5. Lattes prices are under $7. The iced coffee tasted burnt and there was very little flavor seen as how I was charged two times for sweeteners in my drink. I will not be returning. First time here was not enjoyable.

Excelente café!
Rico todo!
Excellent coffee, food and service. We also witnessed a very rude customer and the baristas were kind, calm and did a great job handling the situation. Will return again next time we’re in town!
Good coffee and nice staff!
Such a cute coffee shop inside! Great friendly service! Macarons and coffee delicious!

The coffee is so good and the building is super cute don’t be mislead by it being next to a gas station. There’s also a drive through which is super convenient. Coffee was made super fast and the girl helping us was amazing!!
AMAZING coffee!! Super quick service and the place is adorable :)
Employee was really rude
Recently discovered this little gem and really liked this place. The coffee was delicious and service was excellent! Will definitely be visiting soon again.
It was fast and easy. No judgements or anything. Very nice people who work here.
Great atmosphere! Coffee taste is outstanding!!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Creme Brulee Latte, Cold Foam Snickerdoodle

reviews_data.review_text: Really good coffee. Friendly staff. Decent amount of food options, including ice cream. Also a drive through at this location so that's a nice touch. A decent amount of seating space in the restaurant as well.
Great food 😋 👌🏿 👍🏿

Moved here from Asheville, I’ve missed the amazing food and drink options there but today, I found the BEST!!!! I’ve been to every coffee shop in this area I can find. This is amazing!!!! Absolutely thrilled! Thank you!

My husband and I discovered this little gem of a coffee shop a couple of weeks ago. The coffee was delicious! The breakfast sandwiches were good.  The service was stellar! Having never been there, I didn't know exactly what to order. I was considering the holiday specials, while my husband knew exactly what he wanted. The cashier/barista, Keely, was patient, courteous, and just plain nice! She listened to my preferences, made recommendations, and even customized our drink choices. For example, my husband wanted a vanilla latte. So that's what she made him, but added a splash of white mocha, and he really liked it! There was a moment when I was waiting for our order, and there was a car at the drive-thru and a customer at the register. Keely was working alone. But she remained pleasant and focused on delivering great customer service.
They have a great selection of different coffees and drinks. The staff was very helpful in explaining the different options. Our order came out really fast and they were so good.
قهوة جميله وجلسات لطيفه
Shocking! Had to throw it out.

I’ve gotten iced coffee/ americanos from here and they taste amazing. My fav espresso ever. however, I’ve also gotten a hot americano and hot tea before, and the water is WAYYY too hot. like after I wait 5+ mins with the lid off it’s still piping.
My suggestion is to just get an electric kettle for boiling water. Electric kettles seem to heat to the perfect temp.

I’ve gotten iced coffee/ americanos from here and they taste amazing. My fav espresso ever. however, I’ve also gotten a hot americano and hot tea before, and the water is WAYYY too hot. like after I wait 5+ mins with the lid off it’s still piping.
My suggestion is to just get an electric kettle for boiling water. Electric kettles seem to heat to the perfect temp.
They have great latte's! I get the iced  brown sugar with oatmilk latte' and it is better than you know who's, lol.
Customer service was the best while  visiting

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Coffee Tasting Flight, Espresso Flight, Aero French Press

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful place with wonderful coffee and a kind community ❤️🙏🏼

Overall, I really like this coffee shop as it's close to my home and the people are pretty friendly. My only complaint/ suggestion for the management of this establishment would be that they require whomever is preparing the food to add minimum. Have their hair pinned back today. I found a very long hair threaded through my breakfast sandwich. They were apologetic and did remake my sandwich except for that. I am thankful the young lady who made it prior also remated with her hair Free falling over her shoulders. Aside from this one incident, I do enjoy this coffee shop and will return

I got a white tea passion fruit, but the tea was brewed at too high of a temperature. This takes away the flavor of the tea. And during my visit, the music ended up getting blasted way too loudly. I was trying to listen to my own music while I did reading for my project, but it just got to be too much.
The wife loves this place. It's like a hidden treasure!

It's a cute place but it's not wheelchair accessible. I came with my friend and the ramp is blocked off by some propane tanks screwed into the concrete. We had to bump the wheelchair up and then figure out a safe way to get them off the step. Wheelchair users keep this in mind.

Edit: The owner of the property reached out to explain the tanks belong to the business next door to Waterbean. Although they are blocking wheelchair access to the coffee shop, I appreciate their responsiveness and their commitment to ensuring everyone's safety and enjoyment of the businesses they lease to. I have amended my review due to the fact that the owner has promised to contact the neighboring business to have the tanks removed. I hope my friend and I can visit soon and enjoy our stay without having to worry about accommodating his wheelchair!
My iced chai latte was nice and refreshing. And the service is always great. The ladies that work there are always smiling and friendly.
Boldly adjoined to a gas station! However it was clean and bright, the offerings were  good.

A cozy and chill coffee shop! If it were very busy, seating would feel crowded but it's been pleasantly quiet the 2 times I've visited. I've been on weekdays and it's a good place to study! Good food offered here from bagels to build-your-own sandwiches (with a lovely house aioli offered) and staff is friendly too!!
Loved stepping into this little Gem today. Staff was friendly, space was beautiful and the latte they made me was custom cause I'm picky and it was 100% on point. Thank you!!! I'll be back.
Great little place, highly trendy, decorated amazing and the coffee is great as well!
Had an iced latte with vanilla and Irish cream. I highly recommend it. The interior is an eyesore, however.
Good location to work remote from, outlets and wifi available. Service and coffee were great.
The coffee was average but the service was good and the seating area was updated and clean

The location for this coffee shop is a bit hard to navigate to and parking can be sparse but it’s a great space to meet up with friends. The decor is pretty updated though some areas could use cleaning (vents etc), the coffee is okay and food offerings are minimal but what brings the score down mostly for this coffee shop is the service is not as warm and welcoming as other spots. Generally speaking pricing is much more than Starbucks as well so value for what I purchase is also another negative factor. If I have options I’ll likely go elsewhere but is an okay alternative.
While the customer service was great the coffee was not. We ordered 2 vanilla cappuccinos and we couldn't even taste the coffee. We just poured it out. Very disappointing experience!

HOW this place exists WHERE it does is wild to me. The gas station it's attached to is fine but the whole Attached to a Gas Station is a strange factor when you pull in. Then you walk through a dimensional door into a place with beautiful design, cozy but modern furniture. The staff was friendly, knowledgeable and patient (as I took too long to order because the options were unique and interesting!!)
Was the coffee wonderful? Yes. VERY much so. Beyond the chains of course but even beyond the craft coffee scene too.
What shocked me is the FOOD was good. Coffee shop food in the US is normally microwaved nonsense filled with chemicals and fake flavors, but the bagels and croissants were so excellent, the meat/cheese quality was so impressive.
Ill be back, soon, and often.

I'm disabled and this place, despite the great coffee, fantastic sandwiches and relaxing atmosphere getting inside is ridiculous.  Who thought that the slanted sidewalk entranceway was a good idea. For the disabled this place is tricky.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Tarsha,

We appreciate your support for our business. Please note that the sidewalk in front of our store does not provide handicap access. The handicap access ramp is located in front of the SM Mart, as both buildings are connected. Thank you for visiting and for your ongoing support.

reviews_data.review_text: Visited Waterbean Coffee to do some homework. It wasn’t busy and was quite peaceful. Lots of seating for small and larger groups of people. Very clean, including the bathroom. There is only one bathroom which is unisex. They provide free wifi at this facility. There is a variety of drinks and baked goods to select from. I got a mocha frappe which was delicious. They also have a drive thru if you do not have time to sit down and enjoy your coffee. I will say the location threw me off. It is located beside a gas station but is separate from the facility. Overall I find it family and student friendly. Highly recommend.
Walked in nobody  spoke so I left-
It's not gas station coffee. It may be in a building attached to a gas station, but it is super clean inside. The coffee is excellent and the muffins are delicious.

Driven by many times, had not seen this place
Good coffee, tasty breakfast items and calm quiet atmosphere.
Fair prices and there is a drive through too.
Best Ice Coffee in Charlotte
Great coffee and food, and very nice and helpful employees as well. Would recommend.

The food, coffee, and atmosphere looked fantastic. However the taste of the iced snickerdoodle latte that I ordered was very artificial and syrupy. The food was alright. This was my first time here and the lady who served me had a nasty attitude. She kept rushing me before I even knew what coffee beverage I wanted. Then she was clearly annoyed when I wanted to add food as well. I didn’t even know there was a second menu for the food. I let her know it was my first time there and she didn’t even acknowledge me. Normally, I love supporting local coffee shops, but I will not be coming back. It is really unfortunate.
Great coffee..... they have a large variety of hot & cold brews . I have not tried the food yet, but next visit, I will.
My new go-to place! We needed a place like this in this area, and this one is so so good! Lots of options and unique flavors (my favorite is the Lavender Latte).
Great place to get work done w great coffee. They have unique flavors
Coffee was great
Best coffee spot we have been too so far!

Baristas are so polite, I believe their names are Morgan and kiegha. This is by far best gas station coffee of all time. staff is very nice and the coffee is top notch. by the way, the taco joint at other side of gas station is really good as well.
Great place
Great staff and coffee ☕️. I actually like them better then Starbucks
Service, food and coffee are really good!
Great coffee!  They have some interesting specialty drinks to try but the iced coffee is my favorite.
Incredible coffee!
I love this place, the food is good and so is the coffee!
Mmmmm ice cream!

Have always been a fan of WaterBean coffee outlets around Charlotte area, this one seems to be pretty decent to work too. Very peaceful to remote work during fridays and the weekends. Very well furnished and has good seasonal Latte options. Lavender Honey Latte was amazing 🤩
Love a new coffee joint in the area! Coffee choices are delicious and the breakfast is really good as well. Does not taste like it’s warmed up. This will be a new joint we will be coming to often!
Separate Coffee shop with a drive thru and indoor seating next to a gas station convenience store

Specialty drinks here were good. Atmosphere is similar to other waterbeans. It's fine. Service was ok. Prices are likely on par with others. It's ok, not in a rush to come back. Please add more hot coffee items and specialty drinks, not teas and not all cold brews.
Beautiful inside & out. Amazing coffee, they even have the #1 ranked Colombian bean available! The baristas are lovely, kind, & knowledgeable! This is a must go see!
I got coffee on their first day opened last week. I got a free macaron! Delicious :)
10/10 🤩 their iced chai and bacon, egg and cheese on a croissant was soooooo good! New favorite place 🙌🏼❤️

Been going to other Waterbean locations throughout Charlotte for years and so happy to see their new location when visiting family in Concord! Great coffee, beautiful decor, perfect playlists and vibe, excellent service, and they do an amazing job of maintaining brand consistency in all of their locations in the area. Keep up the awesome work! ☕🙌💕

Just came across this place yesterday, and I had to try it out this morning, and I must say they definitely did not disappoint! The bacon egg and cheese on a croissant and iced chai tea was amazing and that’s on my momma! Staff was very nice and friendly as well!

I went on the grand opening hoping to find a new coffee spot and I definitely did! The baristas were very helpful when I didn’t know what to get. I ended up getting an iced caramel latte and a breakfast sandwich. Almost before I could sit down they were both ready and it tasted amazing! Will definitely make this my new go to coffee spot.
